is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindley" authorityYear="1845" box="[485,611,306,327]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Masdevallia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="278" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosa">M. racemosa</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the blackish leaf petiole (vs reddish), the adaxially hispid sepals (vs glabrous), the obtuse and apiculate dorsal sepal (vs acute and acuminate), and the oblong-elliptic and obtuse petals (vs lanceolate and acute).
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
