<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,158,1372]" pageId="4" pageNumber="281">
Plant epiphytic, litophytic or terrestrial, repent. Roots slender, 
<quantity box="[843,979,158,185]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="281" unit="mm" value="0.7" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.6">0.6–0.8 mm</quantity>
in diameter when dried. Ramicauls stout, erect (0.5–) 
<quantity box="[264,388,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="281" unit="cm" value="2.8" valueMax="3.8" valueMin="1.8">1.8–3.8 cm</quantity>
long, 1.0– 
<quantity box="[508,581,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="281" unit="cm" value="1.8">1.8 cm</quantity>
in diameter, enclosed by 2-3 tubular sheaths. Leaves erect, thickly coriaceous, petiolate, lanceolate, acute, base narrowly cuneate into a blackish petiole, (0.6–) 
<quantity box="[1072,1201,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="1.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="281" unit="cm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="1.9">1.9–2.6 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1280,1419,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="281" unit="mm" value="1.2" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.9">0.9–1.5 mm</quantity>
in diameter; the blade (2.5–) 4.3–6.2 × (0.7–) 
<quantity box="[600,726,266,293]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="281" unit="cm" value="1.7" valueMax="2.1" valueMin="1.3">1.3–2.1 cm</quantity>
. Inflorescence loose, successively one to several flowered raceme, (9.2–)19.5–29.0 cm long; peduncle slender, erect, (6.8–)13.5–25.0 cm long, maroon. Ovary maroon, sulcate, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="281" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="3.5">3.5–4.5 mm</quantity>
long. Flowers one or two open at one time; pedicel 2.0– 
<quantity box="[813,891,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="281" unit="cm" value="2.1">2.1 cm</quantity>
; sepals reddish-orange, sparsely hirsute adaxially; dorsal sepal obovate, 2.0–2.8 × 
<quantity box="[486,626,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.025" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="0.95" pageId="4" pageNumber="281" unit="cm" value="1.025" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="0.95">0.95–1.1 cm</quantity>
, connate to the lateral sepals for 
<quantity box="[984,1111,374,401]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="281" unit="cm" value="1.7" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.6">1.6–1.8 cm</quantity>
, forming a cylindrical sepaline tube, free portion obtuse, apiculate, three veined; lateral sepals forming an obovate, obtuse, emarginate synsepal, 2.7– 3.0 × 
<quantity box="[202,332,446,473]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="281" unit="cm" value="1.75" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.6">1.6–1.9 cm</quantity>
. Petals orange, oblong-elliptic, slightly falcate, obtuse, the labellar half with an elliptical callus, 5.0 mm × 2.0– 
<quantity box="[259,347,482,509]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="281" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
. Lip white with yellow apical margins, obovate, obtuse, straight, margin undulate, sulcate between a pair of low calli, base truncate, 6.0–6.5 × 1.6–2.0 mm. Column whitish-yellow, margin erose, slightly arched toward the apex, 5.0– 
<quantity box="[298,385,554,581]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="281" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[459,546,554,581]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="281" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
in diameter. Anther cap obovoid, papillose, 1.2 × 1.0 mm. Pollinia 2, obovoid, laterally compressed, 1.2 × 
<quantity box="[446,535,590,617]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="281" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
